Keefe, Appellee, v. Youngstown Diocese of the Catholic Church, Appellant.

[Cite as Keefe v. Youngstown Diocese of the Catholic Church (1998), 82 Ohio St.3d 1215.]

(No. 97-1173 Submitted May 12, 1998 Decided June 24, 1998.) Gerald P. Leb and Richard W. Shrake II, for appellee. Newman, Olson & Kerr and Mary Beth Houser; Lesh, Casner & Miller and John R. Frank, for appellant

The appeal is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently allowed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur.
